The Concept Principle is intended to function as described when applied in good faith and in accordance with the author's stated formulation and purpose.

(a) The author stands behind the Concept Principle as articulated and accepts responsibility, in principle, for its correct application when it is followed faithfully and without distortion.

(b) Recipients who modify, omit, extend, or combine the Concept Principle with other systems are responsible for the results of those changes and for any new behavior introduced by their implementations.

(c) Recipients are encouraged to implement the Concept Principle in ways that respect broadly accepted human rights and ethical norms. Uses that intentionally or systematically undermine fundamental rights, or that cause large-scale harm, are outside the intended scope of this license.

